Why CC-BY-4.0 for the specification?

1. Allows anyone to implement the specification without restriction
2. Allows creating derivative specifications with attribution
3. Permits commercial use of the specification
4. Requires only attribution, not license propagation
5. Standard for open specifications (used by W3C, WHATWG, etc.)

For software implementations, use the MIT License in the root of this repository.
